scenes.title: Darul Mawa '93
scenes.description:
Darul Mawa (also known as Jamiyah Children's Home) was a children's home for around 80-100 orphans and underprivileged children aged 3 to 18. Officially opened in 1993 by Jamiyah, it was located in a former school building, Elling North Primary School, leased by the Singapore government. The children living there came from diverse and challenging backgrounds, including those with parents struggling with addiction, and those who had suffered physical violence, mental and sexual abuse, or were orphans.

At Darul Mawa, these children were provided with shelter and care by dedicated welfare staff who nurtured, educated, and prepared them for life beyond the home when they turned 18. The home was visited by notable local celebrities, such as Dangdut queen Rosalina, Pop Yeh-Yeh singer Jefrydin, Koosmangat, legendary football players Fandi Ahmad and Malek Awab, and the late Singapore President Ong Teng Cheong.

In late 1998, the residents and staff were informed by the Singapore government that they had to relocate to make way for a new highway. The building was eventually demolished in 2000, leaving the former residents with memories of their time there but no way to relive them.

This project, spearheaded by MetaRyuk and architect Rizk Ghazaly, aims to digitally restore the building in the metaverse, allowing former residents and staff to relive their memories and show their children what life was like back then.

scenes.title: Metadyne Labs - Rat Scape

Put your strategizing skills to the test and see how fast you can make it through 13 levels of challenges, carefully constructed by the resident mad scientist. The scientist wants to test, not just your agility, but your cunning too. Choose carefully where and how to use your Rat Blaster to open gateways throughout the maze and save precious time to reach the top spot on the leaderboard. Make it through the 13 levels and see if you can collect all 10 rewards—some will be tricky to unlock! Find them all and you’ll leave with 9 Wearables and a special Emote that will ensure you never forget your time in the maze!

In this scene Nikki used AI for every single texture, skybox, NPC dialogue, NPC style concepts, and maze layout on each floor. This entire scene was made in SDK7 with the Visual Studio SDK7 Editor Extension. This is an 8x8 estate. The entirity of this scene was made during the Game Jam duration; nothing here was reused from previous projects. In this lucid dream you journey through the Fortress to discover your true identity and purpose in this universe.

Collect ores and magic stones from mining, farming plants and discover through digging. You can also trade resources for Gold Midas, the currency in the world. Players who pass the admission quiz will be awarded the Sunstaff, a magic staff that gives you the ability to cast spells!
